President Obama expressed his sadness over the passing of Representative Mark Takai. He praised Takai for his dedication to public service and his advocacy for the most vulnerable in society. Obama also commended Takai's support for the military, veterans, and his efforts in cancer research. The President concluded by saying that Mark Takai leaves behind a legacy of courage, service, and hope. He offered his thoughts and prayers to Takai's wife, children, and loved ones.